## Overview

**Description**

Oceanfront Resort set on 50 lush acres at Keoneloa Bay; rooms and suites with garden, ocean or mountain views.

**Location and History**

Forsaking the overblown shenanigans found in many of the larger island resorts, this world-class property favors a more genuine Hawaiian character pegged to the era of Matson steamers and sophisticated leisure.

With no building higher than the tallest palm, this hotel has a low-profile look that disguises an immense range of facilities. (Beware: It can take more than 15 minutes to walk from the spa to a guest room in the Shipwreck Wing.)

Despite the castaway vibe, this hotel lies just 20-minutes' drive from Lihue's breezy little airport (LIH).
